MasterCard Inc., the worldâ€™s second-
biggest payments network, said processed transactions climbed 10
percent globally through Feb. 14 and that it bought back about
300,000 of its shares.  Card spending in the U.S. rose 3 percent and purchases by
cardholders traveling abroad surged 17 percent through mid-
February, Chris McWilton, president of U.S. markets, said today
during an investor conference. The Purchase, New York-based
company bought back about $75 million of shares, he said.
MasterCard is authorized to repurchase $1 billion in stock.  To contact the reporter on this story:
